column1: Heh! We ain't losin' to no phonies!

They may have appeared like us on the surface,
but in the end, they were pale imitations. They
never stood a chance.

No way. How could this happen? How could my
Phantom Thieves lose?
Does that mean... you're the real ones?

Please trust us, Akane-chan! And your father,
too!
None of us would ever give in to injustice!

And no matter what, we never stray from our
chosen path!

You were right. I'm probably the worst dad out
there.

I couldn't avenge Aoi, nor could I carry out my
duties as an officer.
Hell, I... couldn't even talk to you face-to-face.
I was afraid... to lose you.

And so, I turned my back on justice... and buried
the thought of vengeance for Aoi.

All this time, I've been fooling myself, thinking
one day I'd get my chance.
But I couldn't have been more wrong!
So I want to set things right!

I swear that I'll bring those criminals to justice
for what they've done to you two!
And Akane, I need your courage to do it!
Are you really going after him?
Yes! Consider it a promise to your mother!

Then, if it's a promise, I will never, ever forgive
you if you break it.
Don't worry. I never will, Akane.
I believe you... I always have.

I've always been so scared... of losing what's
precious to me.
After Mom passed away, you changed...

You used to be so cool... Then suddenly,
you didn't even want to look me in the eye.

You were never home, either... like you didn't
wanna see me.

But it's okay now. I can tell you want to be the
dad I used to know.

No... This has to be some kind of joke! It has
to be...
Calm down, Wolf. This is how it always happens.

Akane-chan, or should I say Akane-chan's
Shadow, went back to her former self.

That's a sure sign the real Akane will go
back to normal, too. So cheer up, Wolf.

You guys couldn't have mentioned that
sooner?

That display of emotion as you cried your heart
out... It was touching, to say the least.
Mmhm. It made me cry a little, too.
I wasn't doing it for the compliments...
What're you talkin' about? I wasn't crying at all.
Gotta say, you're one helluva dad.

He did everything he could to protect
Akane-chan, even risking his own life.
Would you cut it out? I'm nowhere near that competent.

Mewhehe, are you blushing? All jokes aside,
there's no need to hold back anymore, Wolf.

Together we can strike down any evil, all of us
working as one!

...Never thought a thief could teach me a thing
or two.
But you know what? I made Akane a promise.

To arrest Konoe and Owada and bring this case
to an end!

...Not to backtrack, but what's going on with
Akane in the real world?
Sounds like a plan. We're done here.

Actually, we came here because we heard she
was kidnapped...

Maybe she was never kidnapped to begin with.
It might be good to check if she's at home.
